{
  "stem": "24462.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wanted to mention that Polish prisoners of war in '39 were given the opportunity to leave the camp and to work as a civilian workers in Germany.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would be paid wages, given the ration cards.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they could live in a private rented apartments, houses, or-- or flats, rooms, whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of-- a lot of Polish prisoners of war took the option.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't if this was '41, around '41.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when I arrived in '42, I met a lot of them wearing the P sign, for Pole, and working in different places.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One was a watchmaker, my friend, and one was working in a factory.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One was working-- some of them are working on farms.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But still, they were working, living privately, renting rooms, and earning some-- some money, wages.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they had the ration cards, which were most important.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because you couldn't buy anything in Germany without the ration cards, food ration cards and tax [? style ?] ration cards.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "For-- so they-- a lot of Polish prisoners of war were-- took the option, and they were living like this in  Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I arrived in Germany on the 24th of January, '42.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So just 10 days after leaving [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I did, in Warsaw, I wrote a letter and another letter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I got a message after the war from one of my cousins who survived that they got my-- the message.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But to get into the ghetto, it was impossible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A train was passing the ghetto from one side of Warsaw to the other side, just through the [INAUDIBLE] place.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I decided to take train-- train and see if I can jump or I can get into whatever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was impossible, because the doors were locked.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And guards were everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
